## The problem
In the in-depth (place my order), following the guide steps a user found an issue that when removing (uncheck) a menu item the price goes up instead of goes down:

![pmo](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/109013/63621553-1d894580-c5ec-11e9-87a1-d6b0eabd312a.gif)



## Why?
This [line](https://github.com/donejs/place-my-order/blob/14401d83c6ea6882135f1220a5a4412b0bfa325b/src/models/order.js#L19) in the [toggle](https://github.com/donejs/place-my-order/blob/14401d83c6ea6882135f1220a5a4412b0bfa325b/src/models/order.js#L18) function always returns `-1` because `item` argument passed to the `toggle` function has `DefineMap` as a type while the items in the list have `Item` type.

The `item` argument is passed from `restaurent.menu.lunch` or `restaurent.menu.dinner` which are converted to `DefineMap` on the fly once are received from the backend `API`.

## Solution
- Move `Item` and `ItemList` to their own file
- Define `menu` property in the `restaurent` model like the following:
```js
menu:{
	type: {
		lunch: {
			Type: ItemList
		},
		dinner: {
			Type: ItemList
		}
	}
}
```

## How PMO application is working?
If you have `#` in the wrong place this doesn’t occur because both item and the items in the list are both `DefineMap`s

## What should be done?
- Update the `In-depth` guide with the fixes
- Update `place-my-order` repo

